(;B[qc]C[The san-san (3-3) stone.

It was the traditional starting move a long time ago. Now it is a little out of fashion, but you can still see it every now and then.

This stone secures only a small ammount of territory in the corner (being so close), but is super safe. You do not have to worry about this stone and concentrate on attacking/doing something else.];W[pd];B[qd];W[pe];B[ob]
;W[md]C[One of the possible follow ups. White forces black to take a small corner and hopes for a bigger compensation towards side and center])
(;B[pd]C[The hoshi (star point) stone.

A fairly modern move, that does not guarantee any points in the corner (opponent can invade 3-3 and live easily). It is saying, I will either get a huge corner, or get enough compensation on the outside to make up for it. If you are a more influence (big center moyo) oriented player this move is for you. "click next to see the 3-3 invasion"];W[qc]
