;B[qg]C[White is already alive and can play elsewhere if she/deems it more important])
(;B[qd]C[The 3-4 (famous Shusaku opening move) is sort of a compromise between the 3-3 and 4-4

Saying I want a moderate ammount of territory in the corner, but I want to have some influence on the center as well.])
(;B[pe]C[These moves are also not THAT popular, but still playable. A very center oriented opening. Black is unlikely to get anything in the corner.])
(;B[qe]C[Quite similar to D but threatening a big corner should white not act soon.])
(;B[jj]C[Tengen (center point) is often laughed at as "I don't know what I am doing" move, but it can have it's perks and was also seen in proffesional games at some point.

It is the move should black want to play mirror go, and also can be beneficial for "fighting style" as most ladders will now be good for black (the black stone is a ladder breaker for any ladder headed to the center)])
(;B[dp]C[The first reason to start in a corner is efficiency. You want to secure as much territory as quickly as possible. "Click next"];AE[qj]AB[os][or][oq][op][qo][po][ro][so][rj][sj][qi][qh][qg][qf][re][se]
